<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1355" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1355">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/157a.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Consul <persName type="to">Letcher</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-07">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Gonzalez brothers case. Spanish Government manifesting deep interest.
                                Press for immediate investigation and adequate punishment of those
                                guilty. Please prepare exhaustive confidential report giving facts
                                as you found them, your sources of information, and your own
                                deductions.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>